The paper deals with software requirement selection, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The focus of the paper is on integrating social values into software requirement selection, which suggests that it may also belong to the subfield of cyber ethics (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the imprecision of social values, which could be related to the subfield of computational uncertainty (cs.CE). The use of Integer Programming (IP) suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfield of computer science theory (cs.CS). Finally, the paper deals with the integration of social values into software, which could be related to the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
